result.execSummary:
The defendant Jayme L O'Dash was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jayme L O'Dash is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jayme L O'Dash was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Jayme L O'Dash was found guilty of Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).
  • Jayme L O'Dash was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: of right to seek post conviction relief

Defendant, Jayme L O'Dash appeared with Attorney Martin Jarvis.  Attorney Thomas Henry Frost appeared for the State. State calls case and reviews case. State would move to dismiss 1,  charge out count 2, count 3 and State would amend the criminal companit and add count 4 which is resisting arrest. Court questions Ms. O'Dash. Ms. O'Dash pleads no contest to count 2, 3 and 4.  Court questions Ms. O'dash on the plea agreement/waiver of rights.  The court finds that the def. knowingly and willingly voluntarily waive their rights. Court finds Ms. O'Dash guilty on all counts.  State recommends 1 year probabtion, AODA assmenssent, 10 days in county jail. Atty Jarvis argues, suggests the same recommendation however does not think that jail time is needed. Ms. O'dash does have 2 days credit.
Atty Jarvis asks if jail time, April 14th start date with work release and in Barron County Jail. Ms. O'Dash speaks to the court. Court speaks to Ms. O'dash. 
 
Sentencing- 1 year probabtion concurrent, AODA assessment, withhold sentence. condtions. comply and follow all recommendations of AODA Assessment. Absolute sobriety - no alcohol, no controlled substances, no paraph. No bars/taverns/liquor store unless primary business is a food service. Must work towards her GED/HSED.  Costs on each count.  is entitled to 2 days credit jail time. 
Count 1- is dismissed.
Count 2- costs, 1 yr probation concurrent
Count 3- costs, 1 yr probation concurrent
Count 4-costs, 1 yr probation concurrent
Preliminary hearing on March 14, 2014 at 01:00 pm.
